tStorageDevices.description: This group defines the mass storage devices in this system.

a7001StorageDeviceIndex.name: a7001StorageDeviceIndex
a7001StorageDeviceIndex.description: An index into the storage device table.

a7001Type.name: a7001Type
a7001Type.description: The type of this mass storage device. If 'Other' is used, then the Type Description attribute shall be used.

a7001TypeDescription.name: a7001TypeDescription
a7001TypeDescription.description: A longer description of the storage device. For example: 3.5 inch flexible diskette drive using diskettes with a maximum capacity of 1.44MB. If 'Other' was specified above, then this field shall be used. Otherwise, the contents of this optional field shall not contradict the Storage Device Type specified above.

a7001Sub_identifier.name: a7001Sub_identifier
a7001Sub_identifier.description: The sub-identifier for this storage device (e.g., the device's SCSI logical unit number.

a7001MediaDataBlockSize.name: a7001MediaDataBlockSize
a7001MediaDataBlockSize.description: The size in bytes of the data blocks used on the storage media. If the media block size is unknown or not consistent across the media, then this value shall be zero.

a7001FormattedMediaCapacity.name: a7001FormattedMediaCapacity
a7001FormattedMediaCapacity.description: The total size in kbytes of this storage media after it has been formatted.

a7001RemovableDevice.name: a7001RemovableDevice
a7001RemovableDevice.description: If true, then this storage device is removable (e.g.: PCMCIA device).

a7001DeviceLoaded.name: a7001DeviceLoaded
a7001DeviceLoaded.description: If true, then the storage device is loaded. If the device is not removable, then this value shall be 'TRUE'.

a7001RemovableMedia.name: a7001RemovableMedia
a7001RemovableMedia.description: If true, then the media in this storage device is removable.

a7001MediaLoaded.name: a7001MediaLoaded
a7001MediaLoaded.description: If true, the media in this storage device is loaded. If the media is not removable, then this value shall be 'TRUE'

a7001Compression.name: a7001Compression
a7001Compression.description: If true, the storage device supports compression.

a7001Encryption.name: a7001Encryption

a7002EventIsStateBased.description: The value of this attribute determined whether the Event being reported is a state-based Event or not. If the value of this attribute is TRUE then the Event is state-based. Else the Event is not state-based

a7002EventStateKey.name: a7002EventStateKey

a7007ProtocolDescription.description: Additional description of the protocol described above. If 'Other' was specified above, then this field shall be used. Otherwise, the contents of this optional field shall not contradict the Protocol specified above.

a7007SignalCharacteristics.description: The signal characteristics of the Bus Port being described.

a7007Isochronous.name: a7007Isochronous
a7007Isochronous.description: Indicates whether or not this bus port supports isochronous transfers.

a7007MaximumWidth.name: a7007MaximumWidth
a7007MaximumWidth.description: The maximum width, in bits, of this Bus Port's data path. A value of 1 should be used for serial.

a7007MaximumTransferRate.name: a7007MaximumTransferRate
a7007MaximumTransferRate.description: The theoretical maximum transfer rate, in millions of bytes per second, that this Bus Port is capable of achieving under ideal conditions. A value of zero should be used if the transfer rate is less than 1 million bytes per second. A value of 0x80000000 should be used if the transfer rate is unknown.

a7007MaximumNumberOfAttachments.name: a7007MaximumNumberOfAttachments
a7007MaximumNumberOfAttachments.description: The maximum number of directly addressable entities supported by this bus port's protocol. A value of zero should be used if the number of attachments is unknown.

a7009NumberOfBlocks.description: The total number of blocks (including the check data blocks) contained in this aggregate p_extent. The block size is the same as the storage device associated with this aggregate p_extent. Note: If no redundancy group is associated with an aggregate p_extent, then this indicates the number of p_extent blocks that are available.

a7009NumberOfBlocksOfCheckData.description: The number of blocks contained in this aggregate p_extent to be used as check data. If the Aggregate p_extent is available, then this value shall be zero.

Note: If no volume set is associated with an aggregate ps_extent, then this number indicates the number of blocks that are available.

a7011ProtectedSpaceExtentInterleaveDepth.name: a7011ProtectedSpaceExtentInterleaveDepth
a7011ProtectedSpaceExtentInterleaveDepth.description: This is the number of ps_extents to stripe as a collective set. This value shall be zero except when the ps_extent group is used.
